### 11. Role-Based Access Control `/7`

**✅ Fully Implemented — two layers**

**SQL Layer:**
- Role-scoped views: `vw_FieldOfficerView` (emergency data only), `vw_FinanceOfficerView` (financial data only).
- `sp_AuthenticateUser` returns `UserType` from the `UserTypes` lookup table.

**C# Layer (ASP.NET Cookie Auth + Claims):**

```csharp
// AccountController.cs — claims set at login
new Claim(ClaimTypes.Role, row["UserType"].ToString())

// Controller-level guards
[Authorize]                                          // any authenticated user
[Authorize(Roles = "Administrator")]                 // AuditController (whole controller)
[Authorize(Roles = "Administrator,Finance Officer")] // FinancialController Create/Delete
[Authorize(Roles = "Administrator,Warehouse Manager")] // AddResource, UpdateStock
[Authorize(Roles = "Administrator,Warehouse Manager,Field Officer")] // ConsumeResource
[Authorize(Roles = "Administrator")]                 // ApprovalController.Process()
[Authorize(Roles = "Administrator")]                 // EmergencyController.Delete()
```

**Runtime data filtering:** `ApprovalController.Index()` additionally filters by `RequesterID` for non-Administrators — non-admins can only see their own approval requests.

